Package: cointsmall
Type: Package
Title: Cointegration Testing with Structural Breaks in Very Small Samples
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jérôme", "Trinh", role = c("aut"), 
           comment = "Original methodology and paper"),
    person("Merwan", "Roudane", email = "merwanroudane920@gmail.com", 
           role = c("cre", "ctb"),
           comment = "R package implementation"))
Description: Implements cointegration tests with endogenous structural breaks
    for very small sample sizes (T < 50) following Trinh (2022) 
    <http://thema.u-cergy.fr/IMG/pdf/2022-01.pdf>. 
    Extends the Gregory and Hansen (1996) <doi:10.1016/0304-4076(95)01751-9> 
    test to allow up to two structural breaks with size-corrected critical 
    values computed via surface response methodology following MacKinnon (1991, 
    ISBN:0198283393). The package is designed for macroeconometric studies of 
    emerging economies where data history is limited.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
